review_blob: Dark golden in colour. A very clean/crisp tasting beer with a slightly bitter finish. Nothing about it was overpowering. A well balanced beer.  -Green bottle cap.

A little too stong in my humble opinion. This beer has quite a kick to it. It is about as malted and dark as it gets. It has the aroma and taste of chocolate, malt, coffee and a good deal of alcohol. Not much carbination to it.

This bottle was from batch #10. It poured a deep, cloudy, golden/orange colour. It has a fruity aroma and tastes of a blend of fruits (apple) and spices.  It seems to be quite sugary as well. A very plesant, sweet beer overall.
Pours a very attractive dark, golden-orange colour with a very long lasting beige head. It tastes slightly bitter, with hints of fruit and caramel throughout. Not bad overall.

A very dark beer, pours almost black and tastes great. Incorporated within the flavor are hints of chocolate and coffee. It is a nicely ballanced beer, none of the flavors are too overwhelming. Quite tasty!

Rochefort 10 is an incredibly smooth beer. It pours a very dark brown colour with a large off-white head. It tastes great and incorporates fruty hints throughout. It is very hard to taste any alcohol, which is surprising at 11.3%. The best beer that I have had yet. My only complaints are that its hard to find and fairly expensive.
A very unique tasting beer. Pours a very nice gold colour with a large white head. It is a very fruity/herby tasting beer. Not bad overall.

A great tasting beer. Quite hoppy and malty in taste. It was slightly bitter, but in an enjoyable way. The dark red colour is quite appropriate to the season/name of the beer. A very good beer overall, similar in taste to Arrogant Bastard.

A great beer overall. It has a similar yeasty taste to many Unibroue beers. It is spicy tasting with many fruity hints to it. Deus is a bright golden in colour and is certainly the most carbinated beer that I have ever seen. It is a beer that brings the best of two worlds together and is worth picking up, especially for celebrations or special events.
